      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The Darzens reaction involves a two-step, base-catalyzed condensation of ethyl chloroacetate with a ketone to yield an epoxy ester. The first step is a carbonyl condensation reaction, and the second step is an S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction. Write both steps, and show their mechanisms.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc0VZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b5753dda625c1ff931d003925428ad66b5746810/OChem_23_EC_026.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows cyclohexanone and ethyl chloroacetate using sodium ethoxide and ethanol, forming an epoxy ester product. The epoxy ring is attached to the first carbon of the cyclohexane ring.\">",
